<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1437,454,1804]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1672,1697]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Comments:</emphasis>
The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[530,790,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suspirium">
<emphasis box="[530,790,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Allometopon suspirium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1207,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayensis">
<emphasis box="[1051,1207,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. malayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1222,1380,1672,1697]" captionStart="FIGURES 173 – 183" captionStartId="99.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@99.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 173 – 183. Allometopon malayensis Sasakawa; 173: paler female, photo, dorsal; 174: male, dorsal; 175: same, left lateral; 176: holotype, notum (from Sasakawa (1993 )); 177: darker female, photo, dorsal; 178: same, lateral; 179: Indonesian male, external genitalia, left lateral; 180: same, posterior; 181: same, internal genitalia, left lateral; 182: Malaysian non-type male, external genitalia, left lateral; 183: same, posterior." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258797/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Figs 
<number box="[1278,1380,1673,1697]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="180.0" valueMax="181.0" valueMin="179.0">179–181</number>
</figureCitation>
), but the surstylus of 
<taxonomicName box="[346,493,1708,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suspirium">
<emphasis box="[346,493,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. suspirium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sinuate and narrower apically but with the apex more broadly rounded, the distiphallus is larger and broader and the hypandrium is unusual in outline. Colouration is otherwise quite dissimilar.
</paragraph>
